uries, Maniera Greca in Europe’s Catholic East argues that tradition is repetitive order achieved through reduction and oblivion, and concludes that the sole persistent understanding of the Greek image has been stereotyped as the icon of the Mother of God.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArt, ByzantinexInfluence. 0aArt, ByzantinezLithuaniaxHistory. 0aArt, ByzantinezPolandxHistory. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aReligion and Theology. 7aART / History / Medieval.2bisacsh  aGreek manner, Byzantine art, Morava School, Catholic Church, visual experience, verbal expression, confessionalism, Middle Ages, Early Modern period, Eastern Europe.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076709408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978946298266640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048532704?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048532704423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048532704/original  a978-3-11-076709-4  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131903-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-1319